  "47vnSLcavg": {
    data: {
      text: "[This flow needs to produce valid outputs to calculate fees on the basis on]",
      description:
        "<p>At the moment fee calculator uses proposal.newDwellings.newBuild.number &amp; proposal.newDwellings.changeOfHome.number &amp; proposal.newDwellings.changeToHome.number. This is (presumably) the total net gain of residential units.</p><p>For outside of London take:</p><ul><li><p>total proposed - total existing = total net</p></li></ul><p></p><p>For within London take:</p><ul><li><p>total proposed (new-removed+rebuilt+retained) - existing (rebuilt+retained) = total net</p></li></ul><p>shortened:</p><ul><li><p>new - removed = total net</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Unfortunately </strong>fee categories are more granular than that, with new built dwellinghouses and dwellinghouses resulting from a change of use of a building being different development categories with separate fees. Building 5 new and changing to the use of 5 dwellings has a net gain of 10 dwellings, but a fee of whichever between the two is largest by itself.</p><p></p><p>In short: We need to further specify what a new dwelling results from, then calculate the requirements for fees (granular) separately from the requirements for residential unit information (not granular)</p>",
    },
    type: 100,
  },
