            info: "<p>Your planning officer needs to know what parts of the building or structure you want to demolish so that they can assess the application.<br><br>You need to show this clearly on all relevant drawings. <br></p><ul><li><p>If the project only includes demolition you should mark the areas to be demolished on:</p><ul><li><p>site plan (proposed)</p></li><li><p>floor plans (proposed)</p></li><li><p>elevation drawings (proposed)</p></li><li><p>section drawings (proposed)</p></li></ul><p></p></li><li><p>If the project includes demolition as part of alterations or new structures too you should highlight the areas to be demolished on:</p><ul><li><p>site plan (existing)</p></li><li><p>floor plans (existing)</p></li><li><p>elevation drawings (existing)</p></li><li><p>section drawings (existing)</p><p></p></li></ul></li></ul>",
